{"word":"κοιρανέω","slug":"κοιρανέω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>κοιρανέω</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:κοίρανος'><el>κοίρανος</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to be lord</i> or <i>master, to rule, command</i>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a> <i>to be lord of</i>, <b><a href='S:Hesiod'>Hes.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>; also, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:dative'>dat.</a>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}